Fix issue with handling put requests

When making a PUT request the obj returned by get_object was not being passed to the
mapper.  This was resulting in a new instance to be created instead of the existing one
being updated.
Implement support for PATCH requests

Better handling of implicit Model.id filtering

With more complex queries filtering by filter_by(**{'id': 'foo'}) can lead to unexpected
results when SQA is unable to determine which id we're referring to.
quick fix for allowed methods

Allow Kim error_status to be overridden

If a MappingInvalid is raised from Kim, previously the error status returned was (effectively) hard coded to 422. Now allow this to be passed in request handler params and overridden.
